📧 Group Email Summarizer — AI Automation

> An NLP-powered dashboard that reads real corporate email threads, extracts action items, owners, and topic insights, and presents everything in a single interactive dashboard.

## 🎯 Problem Statement

In modern organizations, email groups generate hundreds of parallel conversations daily. Teams struggle to track action items, identify owners, and follow up on pending tasks. This project solves that by creating a single AI-powered dashboard that makes sense of all ongoing email conversations automatically.

## ✨ Features

- 📥 Reads real corporate email threads from the Enron Email Dataset
- 🤖 NLP-based summarization using sumy LSA algorithm
- 🔍 Extracts Key Topic, Action Items, Owner, Follow-up Dates automatically
- 🚦 Auto-detects Priority — High, Medium, Low based on urgency keywords
- 📊 Interactive 3-tab Streamlit dashboard with charts and filters
- 💾 Export results to CSV with one click
- 🔌 Fully offline — no API key or internet required
- ♾️ Zero quota limits — runs unlimited times


## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Python | Core programming language |
| sumy (LSA) | NLP-based email summarization |
| nltk | POS tagging and owner detection |
| Streamlit | Interactive dashboard UI |
| Pandas | Data processing and CSV handling |
| Regex (re) | Action item and date pattern extraction |


## 🗂️ Project Structure

```
email-summarizer-ai/
│
├── app.py                   ← Main pipeline (run this first)
├── prepare_data.py          ← Extracts 200 clean rows from Enron dataset
├── requirements.txt         ← Python dependencies
│
├── config/
│   └── config.py            ← Settings and file paths
│
├── services/
│   ├── email_reader.py      ← Reads emails from CSV dataset
│   ├── summarizer.py        ← NLP summarization using sumy LSA
│   └── extractor.py         ← Extracts topic, actions, owner using nltk
│
├── dashboard/
│   └── dashboard.py         ← Streamlit dashboard
│
├── utils/
│   └── helper.py            ← Text cleaning and preprocessing
│
└── data/
    ├── emails.csv           ← Input dataset (download separately)
    └── email_summary.csv    ← Auto-generated output



## ⚙️ Setup & Installation

### Step 1 — Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/[username]/email-summarizer-ai.git
cd email-summarizer-ai
```

### Step 2 — Create virtual environment
```bash
python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate        # Windows
source venv/bin/activate     # Mac/Linux
```

### Step 3 — Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### Step 4 — Download nltk data
```bash
python -m nltk.downloader punkt punkt_tab averaged_perceptron_tagger


### Step 5 — Download the dataset
Download the Enron Email Dataset from Kaggle:
👉 https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/wcukierski/enron-email-dataset

Place `emails.csv` inside the `data/` folder.


## 🚀 Running the App

### Step 1 — Extract 200 clean emails from dataset
```bash
python prepare_data.py
```

### Step 2 — Run the NLP pipeline
```bash
python app.py
```

### Step 3 — Launch the dashboard
```bash
streamlit run dashboard/dashboard.py
```

Dashboard opens at 👉 **http://localhost:8501**


## 🔄 System Workflow

Enron Email Dataset (emails.csv)
           ↓
email_reader.py   →   Read & parse email threads
           ↓
helper.py         →   Clean & preprocess text
           ↓
summarizer.py     →   NLP summarization (sumy LSA)
           ↓
extractor.py      →   Extract topic, actions, owner, priority
           ↓
data/email_summary.csv
           ↓
dashboard.py      →   Streamlit Dashboard (localhost:8501)


